│ Understanding the Issue:\nThe transformation produced by SLPVectorizer turns  │
│ a scalar compare chain into vector code that constructs a <4 x i16> with a    │
│ poison in lane 0, truncates to <4 x i1>, ANDs with zeros, then performs an    │
│ icmp on <4 x i1> and finally extracts lane 0. Alive2 reports: \"Target is     │
│ more poisonous than source\" and shows the vector compare result %4 having    │
│ poison in lane 0, which then leads to a poison being returned by              │
│ extractelement. In the original scalar code, all values are well-defined and  │
│ the final result is false (0). The vectorized code introduces poison which is │
│ observable at the return value.\n\n2. Analyzing opt's Log:\n- The pass        │
│ identifies a bundle of 4 compares and their operands, with zexts and ands,    │
│ and decides to vectorize at VF=4.\n- The vectorization path goes through      │
│ BoUpSLP::gather and ShuffleInstructionBuilder machinery. The relevant first   │
│ transformation point (per your breakpoint) is the gather routine at           │
│ operator() (frames 1..6 in your backtrace), specifically creating a           │
│ buildvector from scalars by starting with a vector initialized to             │
│ PoisonValue.\n- The generated target IR uses:\n  %1 = insertelement <4 x i16> │
│ <i16 poison, i16 0, i16 0, i16 0>, i16 %0, i32 0\n  which seeds the vector    │
│ with poison for lanes not immediately overwritten.\n- Subsequent trunc and    │
│ icmp operations can propagate poison according to LangRef rules. Alive2 shows │
│ %4 = < poison, 1, 1, 1 >, meaning lane 0 became poison in the compare,        │
│ ultimately yielding poison on extraction.\n\n3. Root Cause                    │
│ Analysis:\nBoUpSLP::gather initializes the temporary vector with PoisonValue  │
│ (line 13777). This is correct in many contexts where all lanes will be        │
│ overwritten before use, but here the vector is fed through operations (trunc, │
│ and, icmp) where non-overwritten lanes can affect the instruction semantics   │
│ or internal analysis emits vector compares across the entire vector, and      │
│ poison in any lane can be propagated. Even though SLP only needs lane 0 (it   │
│ extracts lane 0), the intervening vector icmp makes the poison in other lanes │
│ observable because poison is contagious. In this minimized reproducer, the    │
│ use of PoisonValue for the initial vector causes a semantics                  │
│ change.\n\nImportantly, SLP's gather code attempts to insert constants first  │
│ and then non-constants, but it leaves unspecified lanes as poison until       │
│ possibly shuffled. In this case, the vector compare is built on the whole     │
│ vector before extraction, and the presence of poison in lanes participates in │
│ icmp result, yielding poison. The source scalar path has no poison, so the    │
│ transformation is incorrect.\n\nThe fix is to avoid seeding the vector with   │
│ PoisonValue in gather when the constructed vector may flow through operations │
│ prior to full lane initialization, or when only a subset of lanes are later   │
│ consumed. Using UndefValue instead of PoisonValue avoids introducing poison   │
│ semantics: undef does not propagate in the same way and matches the intent of │
│ \"don't care\" lanes for build vectors used as intermediates.\n\n4. Proposed  │
│ Edit Point(s):\n- Edit in BoUpSLP::gather to initialize the temporary vector  │
│ with UndefValue instead of PoisonValue.\n  File:                              │
│ llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp\n  Lines: 13777-13778\n       │
│ Current:\n    13776   auto *VecTy = getWidenedType(ScalarTy, VL.size());\n    │
│ 13777   Value *Vec = PoisonValue::get(VecTy);\n  Proposed:\n    13776   auto  │
│ *VecTy = getWidenedType(ScalarTy, VL.size());\n    13777   Value *Vec =       │
│ UndefValue::get(VecTy);\n\nReasoning:\n- UndefValue represents an arbitrary   │
│ value that does not poison dependent computations unless specifically used.   │
│ It is the correct filler for lanes that are not semantically constrained or   │
│ may never be read.\n- In buildvector construction and shuffling scenarios,    │
│ undef for uninitialized lanes is standard and avoids accidental poison        │
│ propagation through operations like trunc, and, icmp.\n- The rest of the      │
│ gather logic already skips inserting poison constants and relies on shuffles  │
│ and masks; switching to undef preserves these behaviors while eliminating the │
│ miscompile.\n\n5. Conclusion:\nInitializing the intermediate vector with      │
│ UndefValue in BoUpSLP::gather prevents unintended poison propagation through  │
│ subsequent vector operations (trunc/and/icmp) before lane extraction,         │
│ matching scalar semantics where the final extracted lane has a defined value. │
│ This change addresses the correctness bug exposed by Alive2 where the target  │
│ was more poisonous than the source and should fix this reproducer without     │
│ impacting other valid vectorizations."})                                      │
