│ ShuffleInstructionBuilder machinery. The relevant first transformation point  │
│ (per your breakpoint) is the gather routine at operator() (frames 1..6 in     │
│ your backtrace), specifically creating a buildvector from scalars by starting │
│ with a vector initialized to PoisonValue.                                     │
│ - The generated target IR uses:                                               │
│   %1 = insertelement <4 x i16> <i16 poison, i16 0, i16 0, i16 0>, i16 %0, i32 │
│ 0                                                                             │
│   which seeds the vector with poison for lanes not immediately overwritten.   │
│ - Subsequent trunc and icmp operations can propagate poison according to      │
│ LangRef rules. Alive2 shows %4 = < poison, 1, 1, 1 >, meaning lane 0 became   │
│ poison in the compare, ultimately yielding poison on extraction.              │
│                                                                               │
│ 3. Root Cause Analysis:                                                       │
│ BoUpSLP::gather initializes the temporary vector with PoisonValue (line       │
│ 13777). This is correct in many contexts where all lanes will be overwritten  │
│ before use, but here the vector is fed through operations (trunc, and, icmp)  │
│ where non-overwritten lanes can affect the instruction semantics or internal  │
│ analysis emits vector compares across the entire vector, and poison in any    │
│ lane can be propagated. Even though SLP only needs lane 0 (it extracts lane   │
│ 0), the intervening vector icmp makes the poison in other lanes observable    │
│ because poison is contagious. In this minimized reproducer, the use of        │
│ PoisonValue for the initial vector causes a semantics change.                 │
│                                                                               │
│ Importantly, SLP's gather code attempts to insert constants first and then    │
│ non-constants, but it leaves unspecified lanes as poison until possibly       │
│ shuffled. In this case, the vector compare is built on the whole vector       │
│ before extraction, and the presence of poison in lanes participates in icmp   │
│ result, yielding poison. The source scalar path has no poison, so the         │
│ transformation is incorrect.                                                  │
│                                                                               │
│ The fix is to avoid seeding the vector with PoisonValue in gather when the    │
│ constructed vector may flow through operations prior to full lane             │
│ initialization, or when only a subset of lanes are later consumed. Using      │
│ UndefValue instead of PoisonValue avoids introducing poison semantics: undef  │
│ does not propagate in the same way and matches the intent of "don't care"     │
│ lanes for build vectors used as intermediates.                                │
│                                                                               │
│ 4. Proposed Edit Point(s):                                                    │
│ - Edit in BoUpSLP::gather to initialize the temporary vector with UndefValue  │
│ instead of PoisonValue.                                                       │
│   File: llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp                       │
│   Lines: 13777-13778                                                          │
│   Current:                                                                    │
│     13776   auto *VecTy = getWidenedType(ScalarTy, VL.size());                │
│     13777   Value *Vec = PoisonValue::get(VecTy);                             │
│   Proposed:                                                                   │
│     13776   auto *VecTy = getWidenedType(ScalarTy, VL.size());                │
│     13777   Value *Vec = UndefValue::get(VecTy);                              │
│                                                                               │
│ Reasoning:                                                                    │
│ - UndefValue represents an arbitrary value that does not poison dependent     │
│ computations unless specifically used. It is the correct filler for lanes     │
│ that are not semantically constrained or may never be read.                   │
│ - In buildvector construction and shuffling scenarios, undef for              │
│ uninitialized lanes is standard and avoids accidental poison propagation      │
│ through operations like trunc, and, icmp.                                     │
│ - The rest of the gather logic already skips inserting poison constants and   │
│ relies on shuffles and masks; switching to undef preserves these behaviors    │
│ while eliminating the miscompile.                                             │
│                                                                               │
│ 5. Conclusion:                                                                │
│ Initializing the intermediate vector with UndefValue in BoUpSLP::gather       │
│ prevents unintended poison propagation through subsequent vector operations   │
│ (trunc/and/icmp) before lane extraction, matching scalar semantics where the  │
│ final extracted lane has a defined value. This change addresses the           │
│ correctness bug exposed by Alive2 where the target was more poisonous than    │
│ the source and should fix this reproducer without impacting other valid       │
│ vectorizations.                                                               │
│ --------------------  END  --------------------                               │
