│ reverting freeze still leaves the original incorrect transformation in the    │
│ reproducer.                                                                   │
│                                                                               │
│ Given the sensitivity around samesign icmp semantics and how SLP constructs   │
│ intermediate <N x i1> compares, a robust fix likely needs targeted handling   │
│ inside SLPVectorizer to either:                                               │
│ - avoid generating icmp samesign on boolean vector lanes (drop samesign in    │
│ that case), or                                                                │
│ - ensure only the lanes that are actually consumed are well-defined before    │
│ the compare, possibly by narrowing the vectorization or freezing/guarding the │
│ specific lane before extraction.                                              │
│                                                                               │
│ This requires a deeper, localized change in SLP’s compare-building path,      │
│ which is non-trivial to safely modify without breaking existing tests. I      │
│ recommend filing this reproducer and error trace upstream and coordinating on │
│ a design-level change for SLP’s handling of samesign with vector i1           │
│ intermediates.                                                                │
